/*
 * Smart_Probe_Test.cpp
 *
 * Created: 17-03-2026 12:43:42
 * Author : cw
 *
 * v9 changes from v8 (which was working):
 *
 * 1. diag_dr captured AFTER reset() from a readback of the actual chip
 *    register — so D: always shows what the chip is really running at.
 *
 * 2. read_sensor() poll loop: removed fixed _delay_ms(1) between polls.
 *    The 1ms delay was added to "not pound the bus" but at 20SPS it means
 *    75 polls × 1ms = 75ms wasted per sample just in polling.
 *    Replaced with a simple busy-poll of checkDataReady() — the I2C
 *    transaction itself (~0.4ms) provides sufficient bus rest.
 *
 * 3. _delay_ms(50) after each sample replaced with a rate-adaptive delay:
 *    - 20SPS: 50ms  (one full conversion period — original value)
 *    - 45SPS: 22ms
 *    - 90SPS: 11ms
 *    - 175SPS: 6ms
 *    - 330SPS: 3ms
 *    - 600SPS: 2ms
 *    - 1000SPS: 1ms
 *    This makes elapsed time actually reflect the configured SPS.
 *
 * 4. Timeout uses millis_count instead of a fixed counter — prevents
 *    the poll loop from running forever if the chip stops responding.
 *
 * Everything else identical to v8.
 */

